The paper deals with the problem of maximizing a monotone submodular function in the streaming setting with a cardinality constraint, which is a classic problem in the field of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The paper also proposes new algorithms that achieve tight approximation guarantees with minimum memory and low adaptive complexity, which are topics of interest in machine learning (cs.LG), data mining (cs.DM), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper discusses the efficiency of the algorithms on real-world data summarization tasks, which involves information theory (cs.IT).
